msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:2
msgid "vtkRenderingVR - Virtual reality support for VTK"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:4
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:6
msgid ""
"The VR module defines an API and support classes for adding virtual reality "
"support to VTK. The OpenVR and OpenXR modules are both subclassed off of "
"this module. For a list of todos and development issues please see"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:10
msgid "https://gitlab.kitware.com/vtk/vtk/-/issues/18302"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:12
msgid "Supported Devices"
msgstr "支援的裝置"

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:14
msgid ""
"The VR module aims to support runtimes that implement the OpenXR or OpenVR "
"standards."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:17
msgid ""
"See [`VTK::RenderingOpenXR` documentation](../OpenXR/README.md) for "
"information on rendering with the modern OpenXR specification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:20
msgid ""
"See [`VTK::RenderingOpenVR` documentation](../OpenVR/README.md) for "
"information on rendering with the legacy OpenVR specification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:23
msgid "Coordinate Systems"
msgstr "座標系統"

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:25
msgid ""
"With VR the transformations between coordinate systems can quickly become "
"confusing. To help with this note that most matrices in the VR code are "
"stored in vtk convention. That is `a = Mx` where x is a column vector in "
"homogeneous coordinates. Matrices are named according to what spaces they "
"transform between. For example PhysicalToLeftEyeMatrix. Some common "
"coordinate systems are listed below in order of coordinate flow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:32
msgid ""
"Note that in vtkMatrix4x4 multiplcations are done from right to left so to "
"compute a matrix from spaces A to C you would do"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:35
msgid ""
"`vtkMatrix4x4::Multiply4x4(BtoCMatrixInput, AtoBMatrixInput, "
"AtoCMatrixOutput)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:37
msgid "Model -> World -> Physical -> Left/RightEye -> Projection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:39
msgid "Model - what an actor's data is in"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:40
msgid "World - common coordinate system for all actors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:41
msgid ""
"Physical - the physical VR space in meters with 0,0,0 being the center of "
"the floor of the room"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:43
msgid ""
"Device - the viewpoint (position and orientation) of a device such as a "
"controller"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:45
msgid "LeftEye (and RightEye) - the viewpoint of the left and right eye"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:46
msgid ""
"Projection - in clip space, the expected output space for vertex shaders"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:48
msgid ""
"The matrices that go between these spaces are as follows and they can be "
"inverted as desired. You will also find some additional matrices that "
"combine some of these transformations into a single matrix for convenience "
"such as VRHMDCamera->WorldToLeftEyeMatrix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:53
msgid "Model -> World = the actor's matrix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:54
msgid ""
"World -> Physical = inverse of VRRenderWindow->GetPhysicalToWorldMatrix()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:55
msgid "Physical -> LeftEye = VRHMDCamera->PhysicalToLeftEyeMatrix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:56
msgid "LeftEye -> Projection = VRHMDCamera->LeftEyeToProjectionMatrix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:57
msgid ""
"Physical -> Device = inverse of VRRenderWindow-"
">GetDeviceToPhysicalMatrixForDevice()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:60
msgid ""
"There are some other matrices used in the camera that are stored in OpenGL "
"format (transpose of VTK format) using an older naming convention. These are "
"names such as WCDCMatrix, the names correspond to"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:64
msgid "MC = model coordinates (same as above)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:65
msgid "WC = world coordinates (same as above)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:66
msgid ""
"VC = view coordinates, world coordinates translated and rotated to the "
"camera, similar to the LeftEye space"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/VR/README.md:68
msgid ""
"DC = device coordinates (device in this context is a GPU, so same as "
"projection coordinates above)"
msgstr ""
